  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite its release in 2020, \"Arrival Cities\" has yet to receive citations or public engagement on platforms such as Wikipedia and Reddit. This limited visibility suggests that while the work may hold significance, it has not yet established a broad academic or public footprint.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Arrival Cities,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2020, is a scholarly text that explores the dynamics of urban migration and its impacts on community development. However, as of now, the book lacks citations in academic literature, indicating that it has not gained traction within the scholarly community.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Additionally, the lack of mentions across high-fidelity platforms such as Wikipedia, Reddit, and others signals an absence of public discourse surrounding the themes and findings presented in the book. This may suggest that the work has not yet resonated with a broader audience or been integrated into public discussions that often accompany significant scholarly contributions.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The available data indicates a commercial linkage to platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, suggesting a potential for wider public reach if effectively marketed. Despite the absence of scholarly uptake, the foundational themes in \"Arrival Cities\" might still provide valuable insights for future research on urbanization and demographic changes.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In this current context, it is important for the authors and publisher to engage in strategic outreach, including promoting the book to relevant academic and public audiences, to unlock its potential impact and drive discussion in both scholarly and community contexts.</p>",
